Raw material: Te doped Fe- Se based superconductor with nominal composition Fe (Se 0.4 Te 0.6 ) 0.82
Sentence: In the present work, we report detailed mag- neto-transport and magnetic investigations (including measurement under hydrostatic pressure) on a Te doped Fe- Se based superconductor with nominal composition Fe (Se 0.4 Te 0.6 ) 0.82 (with a highest reported T c of 14 K) .
On application of a modest amount of pressure, one can achieve T c of a FeSe compound as high as 37 K .

Name: Te,Se
Sentence: The estimated values of H 0 c2 ( ) for some composi- tions of FeSe, Fe(Te,Se) and Fe(Te,S) are reported to be close to Pauli paramagnetic limit H T ( ) = tesla , but for the present composition it is well above H P .
